		<div class="large-8 small-8 columns small-centered">
			<div class="title-sub2">Welcome to</div>
			<div class="name">Hack the Beanpot</div>

			<p>A Bitcoin accepting Keurig built at <a href="https://twitter.com/HackBeanpot">HackBeanpot</a> in the last two days. We tore apart a Keurig, put an Arduino Uno in it with a wifi shield, an IR sensor and some LEDs. We put it back together nicely and added a Bitpay integration. It now makes you a cup of coffee when you pay it in Bitcoin and place your mug in it. Users can also brew with a donated cup of coffee from below.</p>

			<div class="donate">
				<div class="button-m dc"><span class="price"> <span class="free">19</span> <span class="cup"></span></span><span class="text">Donate a Coffee to our Machine</span></div>

